janus-runner has been installed under:

    /opt/janus-runner

janus-runner is installed to run as root because job scripts may need host-level
build tools, sandboxes, or deployment permissions. Only expose trusted job
manifests and scripts.

Next steps:

1. Edit the runner config. If it did not already exist, it was created from
   runner.toml.sample during package installation:

       vi /opt/janus-runner/etc/runner.toml

   Copy the server trust snippet from janus-server:

       /opt/janus-server/bin/janus-server admin runner-key show \
         --format toml \
         --config /opt/janus-server/etc/server.toml

   Paste the resulting [[auth.servers]] block into runner.toml.

2. Add job manifests under:

       /opt/janus-runner/manifests

   Example files are installed under:

       /opt/janus-runner/share/examples/janus-runner

   Copy and edit them before enabling the runner. The example build job expects:

       /opt/janus-runner/jobs/build-app.sh

3. Enable and start the service.

   Either add the package rc directory to local_startup:

       sysrc local_startup="/usr/local/etc/rc.d /opt/janus-runner/etc/rc.d"
       sysrc janus_runner_enable=YES
       service janus_runner start

   Or symlink the rc script into /usr/local/etc/rc.d:

       ln -s /opt/janus-runner/etc/rc.d/janus_runner /usr/local/etc/rc.d/janus_runner
       sysrc janus_runner_enable=YES
       service janus_runner start

Logs are written to:

    /opt/janus-runner/log/janus_runner.log
